<section class="w-full bg-white py-24 md:py-32 flex justify-center px-6" id="philosophy">
  <div class="max-w-[760px] w-full flex flex-col gap-10 md:gap-14">
    
    <!-- Section Heading -->
    <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-[42px] text-center text-[#3cbce6] mb-2 tracking-wide font-serif italic" style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;">
      The Philosophy of De Aurimori
    </h2>

    <!-- Body Text -->
    <div class="text-[#475569] text-[17px] md:text-[19px] leading-[1.85] flex flex-col gap-8 font-serif" style="font-family: 'Lora', serif;">
      
      <p>
        At the heart of every creation lies a silent dialogue between the observer and the observed. We believe that digital space is not merely code and pixels, but an extension of the natural world—a structured landscape where light, shadow, and void coalesce to form meaning.
      </p>

      <blockquote class="border-l-[3px] border-[#c1e8f9] pl-7 md:pl-10 py-1 my-3 text-[#64748b] italic text-[18px] md:text-[20px] leading-[1.7]">
        "Architecture is the learned game, correct and magnificent, of forms assembled in the light."
      </blockquote>

      <p>
        Qarun de Aurimori explores the delicate balance of minimalism and depth. Our approach is reductive yet soulful; we remove the noise to amplify the essence. Every interface we build is designed to breathe, evolving with the rhythm of human intuition rather than fighting against it.
      </p>

      <p>
        This is not just design; it is a manifestation of ethereal aesthetics and structural integrity, woven into a tapestry that honors both the past's permanence and the digital future's fluidity.
      </p>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>
